descriptions.value: "How did I get here?" Such words of power are commonly heard from Dolfrat the Wizard, whose magic is so great that even he cannot grasp it. Indeed, his enemies accuse him of having no magical training whatsoever, pointing to the evidence of his most frequent incantation: "Did I do that?" And should you ever spy the mighty Dolfrat flat on his back in the road, you can be sure his trusty steed Roshinante is somewhere nearby--probably galloping at top speed away from a creaky tree or shadow that resembled a demon of nightmarish power.

descriptions.value: This treasure contains one of the following items, and may give duplicates if you open multiple:

descriptions.name: attribute
descriptions.value: Only an enchanter's forge can bring about such vile augmentations, but no sane enchanter would aid or trust a creature beholden to N'aix's awful desires. It was only with great difficulty N'aix was able to locate a disgraced enchanter's apprentice who held a useful interest in darker arts.

descriptions.name: attribute
descriptions.value:
A powerful hammer used to extract gems that have been socketed into items. This hammer cannot be used on unusual couriers.
	
	This tool can be used from the Item Details page, which can be accessed from the Armory by double-clicking on an item, or by right-clicking on an item and selecting Item Details.
	
	This tool has multiple charges.
